def max_pooling(x, k):
    (N, C, H, W) = x.shape
    H_out = H / k
    W_out = W // k
    pooled_output = np.zeros((N, C, H_out, W_out))
    for i in range(H_out):
        for j in range(W_out):
            h_start = i * k
            h_end = h_start + k
            w_start = j * k
            w_end = w_start + k
            subregion = x[:, :, h_start:h_end, w_start:w_end]
            pooled_output[:, :, i, j] = np.max(subregion, axis=(2, 3))
    return pooled_output
